body.name: HOSTACK Sideboard Buffet Cabinet with Storage, 55" Large Kitchen with 3 Drawers Glass Doors, Modern Farmhouse Coffee Bar Cabinet, Wood Buffet Table Dining Room Cabinet, White
features: 【Ample Storage Space】The buffet cabinet offers diverse storage options to keep your space clutter-free: 55'' wide top accommodates your oft-used items with easy access and provides large workspace, 3 drawers allow small items to stay in order, 2 glass door cabinets and 1 large middle cabinet bring both display and concealed space for different needs

【Versatile Kitchen Cabinet】Whether you are seeking a vintage-inspired buffet sideboard for kitchen, a coffee bar station for dinning room, or an extra cabinet for living room to take crockery, potted plant or overflow items, this modern farmhouse storage cabinet will cover your needs and be an eye-catching complement

【Modern & Farmhouse】Featuring vintage wood grain, pure white finish, antique-look brass handles as well as distinctive glass doors, this sideboard buffet cabinet creates a modern farmhouse flair in a fresh way, which looks right at home alongside coastal or country interiors

【Crafted To Last】Made of high-quality manufactured wood and smooth-gliding rails in exquisite workmanship, this kitchen buffet with drawers boasts reliable stability and durability to withstand everyday use. Thanks to the solid structure, the top of the buffet can hold up to 300lbs. Overall size: 15.7"D x 55"W x 35.4"H

【DETAILS ABOUT ASSEMBLY】The kitchen storage cabinet comes with the labeled parts and detailed instructions for easy assembly. Two people are recommended to install the cabinet due to the large size, the assembly takes about 3 hours. Please feel free to contact us if you need any assistance

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This sideboard is very nice and very sturdy for a fantastic price!! It did take an afternoon to put it together as noted, but it went together easily and without any issues. It holds a ton of items, so we were able to clear out multiple shelves and drawers in the kitchen and reorganize there. This fits in beautifully with our farmhouse decor. We are very pleased with this purchase!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 6, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Well made and easy to navigate instructions. Took time to put together but worth the effort. Top color does make it looks great as where I wanted to place it. Btw; Its at counter height <+/-> which is useful. Middle section's shelf is not adjustable but the side shelves.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful, sturdy, some QC concerns
reviews.reviewText: Overall I am very happy with my purchase. It’s beautiful, sturdy, the perfect height to keep my big dogs off, and has added much needed counter space.Building it was a bit tedious. It took most of the day to build between help from the pups and being a bit 🍃💨. Directions are easy enough to follow with the exception of a few steps where the illustration showed predrilled holes on the outside when they were in fact inside certain parts.I used an electric screw driver, a drill could be too much power to put this together, and at times I screwed bits in by hand for fear of cracking the boards. There are several holes that should have been predrilled a bit wider (around cabinet hinges especially), I ended up widening a few on my own because otherwise the paint and wood would absolutely have cracked if I was too rough.This unit is VERY heavy. I received this a week early (YAY), and thankfully I was home because it had rained. I ended up opening the box to bring in bits at a time since I didn’t have help.Putting on the cabinet doors was an absolute chore. Despite being very careful about aligning the hinges, the doors were still crooked with awful gaps. It took A LOT of adjusting and I had to widen predrilled holes cause it was cracking when I would tighten my screws. I would secure everything, loosen my screws, align the door and then slowly tighten again till I was satisfied. Not all the screws that were anchored in were completely straight by the time I was done- but I don’t care anymore cause they look straight from the outside now.This unit was packaged perfectly. There were several deep dents and gouges in the cardboard and I thought for sure something would have been damaged but it came out entirely unscathed! Very impressed.Overall I’d really like to leave a 4 star review, taking off half a star for some quality control concerns with the tight anchor points, chipping/cracking wood, and another half star for those annoying cabinets that I was eventually able to straighten.
